description_text:
Credit Relationship Manager:
Support in preparation and submission of Credit Proposals (CP) for both existing (Annual Reviews and Amendments) and New To Bank (NTB) clients. Responsibilities include (but not limited to):
Facility structuring;
BIR;
Financial spreads and comments on financials;
Account conduct;
Generate Ratings
Well versed with PREM/Moodys
Directly liaise with customers (in consultation with the RMs) for information / clarifications;
eName checks. 
Monitor:
CP expiries and update database on a weekly basis for expired, submitted and queried CPs;
Upcoming maturities;
Insurance expiries;
Valuation expiries;
Covenant testing 
Communicate:
Liaise with relevant internal and external stakeholders and clients for the following:
Maintain up-to-date operational performance data of the portfolio (LRD, DSCR and OD utilization etc.)
Develop strong working relationship with the clients enabling to engage them freely to resolve issues. 
Excellent rapport with internal stakeholders (Ops, Documentation, Credit Admin and Credit)
